# Kirana Frontend Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your Azure AD credentials

# ============================================================================
# Azure AD (Microsoft Entra ID) Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Required for MSAL authentication (Microsoft Authentication Library)
# 
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Go to Azure Portal (https://portal.azure.com)
# 2. Navigate to "Microsoft Entra ID" (formerly Azure Active Directory)
# 3. Go to "App registrations" → "New registration"
# 4. Name: "Kirana Web App"
# 5. Supported account types: "Accounts in any organizational directory and personal Microsoft accounts"
# 6. Redirect URI: "Single-page application (SPA)" → http://localhost:5173 (for dev)
# 7. Click "Register"
# 8. Copy the "Application (client) ID" and paste below
# 9. Go to "Authentication" → Add redirect URIs for production (e.g., https://kirana.app)
# 10. Under "Implicit grant and hybrid flows", enable "ID tokens" (for hybrid flow)
# 11. Go to "API permissions" → "Add a permission":
#     - Microsoft Graph → Delegated permissions → User.Read (to get user profile)
#     - (Optional) Add custom scope: api://kirana-api/access_as_user (for backend API)
# 12. Grant admin consent for your organization (if using work account)
# 
# Notes:
# - Multi-tenant support: Uses "common" authority endpoint (supports personal + work accounts)
# - Token storage: localStorage (persists across browser tabs)
# - Token refresh: Automatic silent refresh before expiry (1hr default)
# - Redirect URI in prod: Update in Azure Portal when deploying to production

# Azure AD Application (Client) ID
# Example: "12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789abc"
VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-azure-ad-client-id-here

# ============================================================================
# Backend API Configuration
# ============================================================================
# Base URL for Kirana API (Azure Functions backend)

# Development (local backend)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:7071/api

# Production (Azure Functions)
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://kirana-api-prod.azurewebsites.net/api

